review_blob: Aroma: citrus and pine. Appear: Pale yellow to slightly golden. White head dies quickly. Taste: Medium bitter to light sweet. Palate: Medium to light body. Average carbonation. Slightly bitter finish.

11.2 oz. bottle. Labeled as Monks Cafe Flemish Sour Ale.  Less sour in the bottle than from the tap. Mild sour, doughy nose. Copper color. Tan head. Light sweet and sour taste. Medium body. Lively carbonation.
